<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4183] AMQ 5.7 lost long queue names with filteredKahaDB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4183</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using AMQ 5.7 with filteredKahaDB and perDestination=&quot;true&quot;. I send persistent messages to a queue with a long name (more than 60 chars in the name). After broker restart this queue is not there anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that kahadb is generating a truncated directory for that queue. The directory name is missing first letters. For short queue names, directory start with something like &quot;queue#3a#2f#2f....&quot;, but for long queue names directory start with &quot;#2f#2f...&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux, AMQ 5.7, KahaDB, filteredKahaDB, perDestination=&quot;true&quot;, long queueNames.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12617003">AMQ-4183</key>
