                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13502572" author="alisenberg" created="Thu, 22 Nov 2012 04:07:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Setting system properties MaximumDirNameLength (defaults to 200) and MaximumFileNameLength (defaults to 64) to a higher value solved the problem. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13503787" author="tabish121" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 14:08:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like a non-issue then.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13503824" author="alisenberg" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 15:07:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you don&apos;t set those system properties and still use long queue names, then there is no warning or error alerting those queues will disappear after broker restart. One solution would be controlling the length of queue names while creating them and verifying against MaximumDirNameLength and MaximumFileNameLength.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;adrian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530042" author="tabish121" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 15:42:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a warning to inform of name truncation in mKahaDB when filenames exceed the system property value&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
